<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-11T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-11T10:00:00-05:00" n="1003" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1003">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2938</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WS1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-11T16:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">October
                                            11, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi></date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 8.37 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2977. Referring to my cable 2935, October 1, 1 p.m. Esthonian
                                delegates here have informed me that they no longer desire
                                    <persName>Ferdinand Kull</persName> to proceed to the United
                                States as their representative and his request for visa is therefore
                                withdrawn.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_WS1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Whitehouse</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>